Power BI â€“ Calculated Column vs Measure vs Power Query
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. Storage & Calculation:
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Calculated Column: Stored in the data model, increases file size. Calculated once during refresh.
Measure: Not stored, only formula kept. Calculated on the fly when used in visuals.
Power Query: Transformation done before loading into model (ETL).

2. Filter Context Behavior:
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Calculated Column: Ignores slicers/filters (values donâ€™t change).
Measure: Respects slicers/filters (dynamic values).
Power Query: Static, fixed before load.

3. Use Case Scenarios
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scenario 1 â€“ Categorizing rows
Need: Mark orders as â€œBigâ€ if Amount > 250.
Solution:
-----------------------------------------------
"Calculated Column â†’
IsBig = IF(Sales[Amount] > 250, "Yes", "No")"

Stored permanently, useful for slicers/filters.
-----------------------------------------------
Scenario 2 â€“ Total Sales
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Need: Show sales total by Customer, Region, or Month dynamically.
Solution:

Measure â†’

Total Sales = SUM(Sales[Amount]
Always recalculates based on filter context.
-----------------------------------------------
Scenario 3 â€“ Splitting Date Column
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Need: Extract Year, Month, Day for filtering.

Solution:

Power Query â†’
Add â€œYearâ€, â€œMonthâ€ columns before loading â†’ keeps model clean & optimized.

4. Performance
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Calculated Column: Heavy (stored values). Avoid unless necessary.
Measure: Light (calculated only when needed). Best practice for KPIs.
Power Query: Efficient for data prep, reduces model size.

5. Golden Rule
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Power Query â†’ Data cleaning, transformations.
Calculated Column â†’ Row-level fixed logic needed inside model (e.g., classification, flags).
Measure â†’ Dynamic aggregations, KPIs, comparisons (best for visuals).

